    ("read", "re_disassemble_range", _t.disassemble_range, "Disassemble a RAW ADDRESS + LENGTH byte range in the sandbox (radare2) — NO function needed, for a CFG blind spot BOTH backends miss. Reach for this when re_disassemble (by name/address, needs a defined function) and re_decompile_at (the function containing an address) both return 'not found' because no function is defined there — the only way to read the instructions when the call graph has a hole. Disassembles `length` bytes from hex `address` (default 256, clamped 1–8192), or `count` instructions if given (clamped 1–1024). QUERY: records an Observation; adds no graph nodes. A long listing is truncated to max_chars with a marker naming both recovery paths (re-call with a bigger max_chars, or obs_get for the full body).",
     {"type": "object", "properties": {"target_id": {"type": "string"}, "address": {"type": "string", "description": "hex start address, e.g. 0x67158"}, "length": {"type": "integer", "description": "bytes to disassemble (default 256, clamped 1–8192)"}, "count": {"type": "integer", "description": "instructions to disassemble (overrides length; clamped 1–1024)"}, "max_chars": {"type": "integer", "description": _MAX_CHARS_DESC}}, "required": ["target_id", "address"]}),
    ("read", "re_reanalyze", _t.reanalyze, "Re-run a target's analysis at a HIGHER depth (busting the cached analysis) so a function or call edge the fast pass missed gets a second chance — use when re_list_functions/re_decompile_function look incomplete (missing a function you expect, or empty callees). QUERY: refreshes the inventory and records an Observation; adds no graph nodes.",
     {"type": "object", "properties": {"target_id": {"type": "string"}}, "required": ["target_id"]}),
    ("read", "re_recover_constant", _t.recover_constant, "Recover the CONSTANT/key a self-contained routine derives at runtime (a license code, an XOR key, a decoded string) by EMULATING it in Ghidra's P-Code interpreter IN THE SANDBOX — the JVM interpreter, never native execution, no network. Use when a value never appears as a literal and re_decompile_function shows only the arithmetic that computes it. ENRICH: on success tags the value onto the function node (attrs.recovered_constant) and records an emulation Observation; adds no new graph nodes. Best on a SELF-CONTAINED, parameterless routine — one taking arguments is emulated over uninitialized inputs and usually won't reach a clean ret, so it yields no recoverable value; when the recovered signature shows args it RETURNS EARLY without emulating (skipped=arg_dependent) and points you at re_solve_constraint. Gated: features.emulation (+ Ghidra headless; returns available=false when Ghidra is off).",
     {"type": "object", "properties": {"target_id": {"type": "string"}, "function": {"type": "string", "description": "the self-contained routine to emulate"}}, "required": ["target_id", "function"]}),
